## Nutrition Protocols (70kg)

**Protocol A — Pre + After** (sessions 75-95 min, moderate-high intensity)
- Before (60-90 min pre): 30-40g HBCDs in 400-500ml water, OR 60-70g cream of rice dry weight (~45-55g carbs) eaten 90-120 min before
- After: 500-1000mg sodium electrolytes + 5g L-glutamine in water

**Protocol B — Pre + During + After** (HIIT 75+ min, long runs 90-120 min)
- Before (60-90 min pre): 30-40g HBCDs in 400-500ml water, OR 60-70g cream of rice dry weight (~45-55g carbs) eaten 90-120 min before
- During: 1 gel (25g carbs) midway through session
- After: 500-1000mg sodium electrolytes + 5g L-glutamine in water

**Protocol C — Pre + During + After** (long runs 120+ min, OCR simulations, race rehearsals)
- Before (60-90 min pre): 30-40g HBCDs in 400-500ml water, OR 60-70g cream of rice dry weight (~45-55g carbs) eaten 90-120 min before
- During: 1 gel (25g carbs) every 30-35 min, starting at 25-30 min — aim for 45-50g carbs/hr
- After: 500-1000mg sodium electrolytes + 5g L-glutamine in water

**Race Day Protocol** (3-hour effort)
- Before (90 min pre): 30-40g HBCDs in 400-500ml water, OR 60-70g cream of rice dry weight (~45-55g carbs) eaten 2 hours before
- During: 1 gel (25g carbs) every 20-25 min from 25 min in — aim for 60g carbs/hr. Sip electrolytes at water stations.
- Immediately after: 500-1000mg sodium electrolytes + 5g L-glutamine in water
